						<div class="postbody">Just read through the code and it all <em>seems</em> OK to me. It would be a good idea to probably rewrite the entire CPU code and fix that bug now, rather than leaving until later on when it will **** up all other emulated components.<br /><br />For a massive performance boost and to make your code smaller and more readable, please read this guide about deferring status flags calculation (written by blargg). I know that you haven't written the CPU with performance in mind <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" />.<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.slack.net/~ant/nes-emu/6502.html">http://www.slack.net/~ant/nes-emu/6502.html</a><!-- m --><br /><br />For instance, here is my AND code for all 8 AND opcodes (A and DataBus are 8bit unsigned). Compare that with what you have written and you will see what I mean;<br /><br /><tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">N = Z = A &amp;= DataBus;</tt></div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.jamesturner.de/">http://www.jamesturner.de/</a><!-- m --></div>
